[CLS] [SEP] ( CNN)Police in the Indian city of Malegaon , in the western state of Maharashtra , are requiring identity cards for an unusual group of residents : Cattle . [CLS] [SEP] Following a recent state - wide ban on the sale and consumption of beef , authorities in the city have asked residents to take a ' mugshot ' of their cattle and submit it to the police . [CLS] [SEP] Along with the photograph , the residents have to give information about their animal 's ' unique features , ' such as the coloring and age of the cow , along with the length of its tail and other distinctive characteristics . [CLS] [SEP] Police officials believe this is the only way to solve cow slaughter cases and enforce the law . [CLS] [SEP] Cows are considered holy and revered by that state 's majority Hindu population . [CLS] [SEP] " We are creating a database . [CLS] [SEP] If we get an information of a cow slaughter , we can quickly go to the resident 's place and check whether it is there or not " , Mahesh Sawai , Deputy Superintendent of Malegaon Police told CNN . [CLS] [SEP] " I believe this will be very effective " So far over 100 owners have complied with the police order and more are lining up outside police stations across the city to get their livestock photographed . [CLS] [SEP] The ruling came in the wake of a recent case of cow slaughter in Malegaon , where two men have been charged for killing the animal and and selling its meat . [CLS] [SEP] The Maharashtra Animal Preservation Bill now includes bans on the killing of bulls and bullocks in its list of non - bailable offenses . [CLS] [SEP] Even the consumption or sale of beef could now land you in prison for five years . [CLS] [SEP] The slaughter of buffaloes , however , is still permissible . [CLS] [SEP] However , beef traders in the country strongly reacted to the decision and called a month - long strike , which ended Wednesday . [CLS] [SEP] The traders refused to even slaughter buffaloes and deprive the state of all bovine meat . [CLS] [SEP] They have now vowed to file a case in the state 's high court . [CLS] [SEP] Red meat lovers were n't too delighted either , arguing the government does n't have a right to interfere in an individual 's personal preference . [CLS] [SEP] Maharashtra is not the only Indian state to tighten its laws on cow slaughter . [CLS] [SEP] Haryana state has implemented a maximum punishment of 10 years in prison , the toughest penalty in the country . [CLS] [SEP] Rajnath Singh , India 's Home Minister has promised that he would do all to devise a country - wide law against cow slaughter .